obo:ECO_0000314  a  owl:Class .

gomodel:SYNGO_1793  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: Consistent with their direct physical association, stonin 2 and synaptotagmin 1 were colocalized at synapses in cultured rat cortical neurons (Figure 1B). The presynaptic distribution of stonin 2 at synaptotagmin 1-immunopositive sites was even more apparent in primary neurons transfected with EGFP-stonin 2.. Experimental description: Legend to figure 1, \"Consistent with their direct physical association, stonin 2 and synaptotagmin 1 were colocalized at synapses in cultured rat cortical neurons (Figure 1B)\".\n\n17/11/2017 Pim\n- The species of the stonin 2 protein is not explicitly stated in the paper. Authors were contacted (haucke@fmp-berlin.de, dd. 17/11/2017). Authors replied:\n\nDear Pim,\n\nIn the study you refer to we used human Stonin 2 cDNA. Sorry for this omission.\n\nSincerely,\nVolker\n\n- Annotation to rat was made for the endogenous protein addressed by the antibody." ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0001-7806-5662" ;
        dc:date           "2017-11-29" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_CC_1793" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10116" .

